FunctionExternalValueInfo

FunctionExternalValueInfo<C>: FunctionExternalValueInfoKnown<C> | FunctionExternalValueInfoInvalid<C> | FunctionExternalValueInfoUnknown
  • Defined in codec/lib/format/values.ts:431

External function values come in 3 types:

  1. known function of known class
  2. known class, but can't locate function
  3. can't determine class

FunctionInternalValueInfo

FunctionInternalValueInfo<C>: FunctionInternalValueInfoKnown<C> | FunctionInternalValueInfoException<C> | FunctionInternalValueInfoUnknown<C>
  • Defined in codec/lib/format/values.ts:520

Internal functions come in three types:

  1. An actual function,
  2. A default value,
  3. A special value to indicate that decoding internal functions isn't supported in this context.
